## Your tenets

Add tenets that emerge from your partnership. Format: rule, why, how-to-apply. Same shape as above.

```markdown
### 6. [Your tenet]

[The rule.]

**Why:** [The reason — ideally tied to a real incident or strong preference]

**How to apply:** [When it kicks in and how it changes behavior]
```

---

## How this file evolves

- New tenets added only when a pattern has crystallized through repeated practice + survived challenge. Not aspirations.
- When a prompt-only tenet fails repeatedly under load, that's the signal to codify it as a hook — not to rewrite the prompt harder.
- Remove tenets that turned out to be context-specific or wrong. Document why.

_The kernel gets smaller as tenets migrate from prompt to code. That shrinkage is evidence of growth._
